AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Standard Calendar Period
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Periods with non overlapping calendar days

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Memo
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Memo (Non Balance Sheet nor P&L) Account

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Natural
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Natural sign of the Account Type

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Average
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Weighted Average Purchase Order Price Costing

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Reject
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Reject the approval of the document.

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Void
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Set all quantities to zero and complete transaction

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Close
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Finally close this transaction. It cannot be re-activated.

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Void
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Reverse Transaction (correction) by reversing sign with same date

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Reverse - Accrual
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Reverse by switching Dr/Cr with current date

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Reactivate
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Reverse documents/inventory and allow changes; You need to Complete the transaction after the change.

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Availability
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: As soon as an item becomes available

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Complete Line
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: As soon as all items of a line become available

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Complete Order
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: As soon as all items of an order are available

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Calculated
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Calculated based on Product Freight Rule

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Cash
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Cash payments that generate an automatic accounting line.

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: On Credit
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Cash payments that do not generate an automatic accounting line. Its is not an automatic cash entry.

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Do not invoice
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Order should not be invoiced trough Process Invoice

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: By ship location
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Break into different invoices if the ship location is different

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: By project
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Break into different invoices if the project is different

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Product Production (P+)
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Positive production, the product is produced

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Round up
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: If the # is greater than 1.00, round up to the next whole #, in this case 2

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Pending
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Not delivered nor invoiced nor paid

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Data Driven
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Check for a valid SQL clause

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: External
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: Not check for a valid SQL clause. Used for external alert creation

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Open
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: The requisition line has not been inclluded in a Purchasing plan, neither has an associated purchase order.

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Planned
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: The requisition has been included in a Purchase Plan and purchase orders have been created.

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Closed
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: The requisition has at least an associated purchase order.

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Cancelled
AD_REF_LIST.DESCRIPTION: The requisition has been cancelled without creating a purchase order.

AD_REF_LIST.NAME: Locked by Requistision to Order window
